# .trivyignore
# Path Traversal in jaraco.context (vendored in setuptools).
# Not exploitable in Veritensor CLI context as setuptools is a build dependency.

# False Positive: Vulnerability only affects Docker CLI on Windows. Our container is Linux-based.
CVE-2025-15558

# Not Exploitable: gRPC authorization bypass affects servers. Cosign acts only as a gRPC client.
CVE-2026-33186

# Not Exploitable: PATH hijacking requires existing shell access to modify environment variables.
CVE-2026-24051
CVE-2026-39883

# Accepted Risk: DoS via crafted JWE. Cosign only processes our own trusted signatures in CI/CD.
CVE-2026-34986
CVE-2026-29181

# --- Cosign Go Binary False Positives ---
# Justification: Veritensor uses the cosign binary strictly as a local CLI tool 
# for signing artifacts with local PEM keys (--key flag). 
# We do not expose SSH servers, parse untrusted HTML, or use Keyless (Fulcio/Rekor) infrastructure. 
# These CVEs are present in the compiled binary dependencies but are NOT exploitable in our execution context.
CVE-2026-49478
CVE-2026-48702
CVE-2026-39828
CVE-2026-39829
CVE-2026-39830
CVE-2026-39831
CVE-2026-39832
CVE-2026-39835
CVE-2026-42588
CVE-2026-46595
CVE-2026-46597
CVE-2026-25681
CVE-2026-27136
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39821
CVE-2026-42508
